olive oil
1 avocado
1 tin sweetcorn
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet tomato sugo
15 g butter
1 tsp brown sugar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
½ packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and roughly chop.
• Drain sweetcorn.
Little cooks: Help drain the sweetcorn!

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly
browned, 4-5 minutes.
• In a medium bowl, combine charred corn, avocado and a drizzle of white
wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,
4-5 minutes.
• Add Tex-Mex spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add tomato sugo, the butter, brown sugar and a splash of water and cook
until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts
until warmed through.

• Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Fill tortillas with some Mexican beef and pork, shredded cabbage mix and
avocado salsa.
• Drizzle with Greek-style yoghurt and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar
cheese to serve. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!